# Agent Safety Rules

## Verification Before Action

- Before importing a package, verify it's installed: check `package.json` or run `pnpm list <package>`.
- Before using a framework API, confirm the version. This project uses Next.js (App Router), NestJS, Prisma.
- Never assume a file or function exists — search or read first.

## Code Quality

- Never leave placeholder code (`// TODO: implement`, `// ...rest of the code`). Implement fully or explain why you can't.
- Never generate fake data, mock API keys, or dummy credentials in committed code.
- Never silence errors with empty catch blocks.

## Security

- Never commit `.env` files, API keys, or secrets.
- Never delete config files (`package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `prisma/schema.prisma`, `docker-compose.yml`) without confirmation.
- Always encrypt sensitive fields (API keys, tokens) before storing in the database.
- End-user endpoints must never expose agent system prompts or admin-only data.

## Git Discipline

- Don't commit unless asked. Don't push unless asked.
- Don't amend commits that have been pushed.
- Write clear commit messages describing the "why", not the "what".

## Architecture Decisions

- Read `docs/SCOPE.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, and `docs/MVP.md` before proposing structural changes.
- Don't introduce new dependencies without justification. Prefer what's already in the stack.
- Respect the persona split: admin features in `(admin)/` routes, user features in `(dashboard)/` routes.
